### 1. Define Zone and Interfaces

~~~
!@UTM-PH
conf t
 zone security OUTSIDE
  desc PUBLIC_INTERFACE
 zone security INSIDE
  desc LOCAL_LAN
 zone security DMZ
  desc SECURE_PUB_SERVERS
 !
 int g1
  zone-member security OUTSIDE
 int g3
  zone-member security INSIDE
  end
~~~


&nbsp;
---
&nbsp;


### 2. Create an ACL to match traffic rules

~~~
!@UTM-PH
conf t
 no ip access-list extended IN-TO-OUT
 ip access-list extended IN-TO-OUT
  permit ip any any
 no ip access-list extended OUT-TO-IN
 ip access-list extended OUT-TO-IN
  permit ip any any
  end
~~~


&nbsp;
---
&nbsp;


### 3. Group traffic using Class Maps

~~~
!@UTM-PH
conf t
 class-map type inspect match-any CM-IN-OUT
  match access-group name IN-TO-OUT
 class-map type inspect match-any CM-OUT-IN
  match access-group name OUT-TO-IN
  end
~~~


&nbsp;
---
&nbsp;


### 4. Define Policy Maps to specify what to do with the traffic.

~~~
!@UTM-PH
conf t
 policy-map type inspect PM-IN-OUT
  class type inspect CM-IN-OUT
   inspect
  class class-default
   drop log
   exit
  exit
 policy-map type inspect PM-OUT-IN
  class type inspect CM-OUT-IN
   drop log
  class class-default
   drop log
   end
~~~


&nbsp;
---
&nbsp;


### 5. Define Zone-Pairs to link source and destination zone to policies in a specific direction.

~~~
!@UTM-PH
conf t
 zone-pair security ZONE-IN-OUT source INSIDE dest OUTSIDE
  service-policy type inspect PM-IN-OUT
 zone-pair security ZONE-OUT-IN source OUTSIDE dest INSIDE
  service-policy type inspect PM-OUT-IN
  end
~~~


